        {
          "content_hash": "d0f0f849b56e76e1",
          "style": "NORMAL_TEXT",
          "text": "I worked with both Dr. Xie and Dr. Ding, and I was one of the students affected during that transition period. It was honestly a difficult position."
        },
        {
          "content_hash": "39db2bcd3373c566",
          "style": "NORMAL_TEXT",
          "text": "I don’t think that characterization is generalizable. From my perspective, it was more of an unfortunate mismatch — in terms of working style and how people understand the advisor–advisee commitment."
        },
        {
          "content_hash": "7af03f0d122c65d6",
          "style": "NORMAL_TEXT",
          "text": "For the 'quit' rates, I’ve heard smaller figures myself. Such figures also don’t capture the full context."
        },
        {
          "content_hash": "f808e21a7c12b733",
          "style": "NORMAL_TEXT",
          "text": "For the funding situation, it was a complicated situation. It involved multiple parties and broader departmental factors. My impression was that Dr. Ding tried to support students within all those constraints while handling things professionally with her colleagues."
        },
        {
